A number of businesses in the tourism sector will reopen under advanced level 3 lockdown. Tourism is one of the sectors hard-hit by COVID-19 lockdown regulations. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - SA Tourism CEO Sisa Ntshona says it will be a while before things get back to normal in the tourism sector. This despite the announcement that some businesses can reopen under advanced level 3 of the lockdown. WATCH: Minister outlines lockdown regulations for tourism sector The sector has been hard-hit by COVID-19 regulations. Ntshona said most of the sector is off-peak and the sector needs to use the winter season to gear up. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.